*All torrents scanned with:
1- Norton Internet Security

Also scanned with reputed antispyware software. Reported malware

There's also Sandboxie to test things. Funny thing is that all my av scan reports never are the same as with free online scanners. And that's no surprise, cause you can't get the same thing for free while there are paid versions. Free online av scanners generate may more fake warnings and false positive because they're basicly using free and/or outdated av signatures.

Good news all!
I just installed Eset Smart Security 4.0.437 in Windows 7 Pro SP1 64-bit, disabled self-defence, restarted Win 7, temporaily disabled NOD32 real time protection to prevent it from quarantining the TrialReset EXE (as NOD32 will so keep the RAR file handy), ran the TrialRest, and it said it was successful.  I then ran the NOD32  manual update, got timed out, kept trying (this is normal Eset behavior), got a link into the update server, it downloaded and installed all updated, and all is perfect.   Great job RH!

Anyone who says the RH puts up files that don't work are full of sh!t.  I'm still running NOD32 on XP with RH's Trial reset from January 2007 and (as I left the watermark on) it still today says I have 30 days left on my trial Nod32 v4.   I started in 2007 with NOD32 v3, updated to v4 when it came out, and the RH supplied trial reset v2.3 still works perfectly.  Keep up the great work RH!
